#
# WHAT IT IS
#   Passwall Server is "the core backend infrastructure for the
#   Passwall platform" — a self-hosted password manager backend
#   that stores and serves credentials to Passwall's mobile
#   (Android / iOS) and desktop / web clients over an HTTPS API.
#   It persists vault data to PostgreSQL with per-user
#   AES-256-GCM envelope encryption, manages user authentication
#   via JWT, sends transactional email via SMTP, and tracks
#   subscription billing through Stripe (`stripe-go v81`) for
#   the hosted-tier product.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/passwall-server/
#                       main.go `showVersion()` plus the
#                       env-driven `applyWorkDir()` — passwall-
#                       server takes minimal command-line args
#                       and is configured almost entirely via
#                       environment variables)
#   passwall-server [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -v, --version                  Print version, commit ID,
#                                    build ID, and build time
#                                    then exit
#
#   Environment (selected most-used):
#     PW_WORK_DIR                    Working directory the
#                                    server chdirs into at
#                                    startup
#     PW_SERVER_PORT                 HTTPS listen port
#     PW_DB_*                        PostgreSQL connection
#                                    (host, port, name, user,
#                                     password, sslmode)
#     PW_SMTP_*                      Outgoing SMTP transactional
#                                    email configuration
#     PW_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY           Stripe secret API key for
#                                    the hosted-tier billing
#                                    pipeline
#     PW_STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET       Stripe webhook signing
#                                    secret
#     PW_JWT_*                       JWT signing key + TTL
#                                    settings
#     PW_PASSPHRASE                  Master passphrase for the
#                                    AES-256-GCM key wrapping
#     (plus dozens more — see pkg/constants and the README for
#      the full list)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/stripe/stripe-go/v81
#   v81.4.0` declared in go.mod — `stripe-go` is THE canonical
#   Go Stripe SDK officially maintained by Stripe (stripe/
#   stripe-go, 2.5K+ stars, the production Go client used by
#   every major Go billing/payments integration; the Go
#   counterpart of stripe-node / stripe-python / async-stripe).
#   stripe-go exposes the typed `stripe.Client` constructor
#   with `stripe.NewClient(apiKey, opts...)`, the entire
#   `stripe.V1Services{}` / `stripe.V2Services{}` typed-method
#   tree covering all 100+ Stripe API resources (Customer,
#   Subscription, Invoice, PaymentIntent, PaymentMethod,
#   Setup Intent, Checkout Session, Price, Product, Coupon,
#   Discount, Refund, Charge, Account, Account Link, Balance
#   Transaction, Usage Record, Subscription Schedule, Invoice
#   Item, Payment Link, ApplePayDomain, Tax Rate, Tax Code,
#   Reporting Run, Reporting Report Type, …), the typed
#   `stripe.<Resource>Params` / `stripe.<Resource>ListParams`
#   builder structs, automatic pagination via
#   `client.<Resource>s.List(...).Iter()`, the typed
#   `webhook.ConstructEvent(payload, sig, secret)` signature-
#   verification helper, the typed `Event` model covering
#   200+ webhook event types, and idempotency-key auto-
#   injection via context.  passwall-server's `internal/
#   stripe` package builds a `stripe.NewClient(...)` against
#   `PW_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` and routes both subscription
#   provisioning / cancellation and `customer.subscription.
#   updated` webhook events through the typed model.
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/passwall/passwall-server/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/stripe/stripe-go/v81 v81.4.0
#       → module github.com/passwall/passwall-server
#     gh api repos/passwall/passwall-server/contents/cmd/
#         passwall-server/main.go
#       → for _, arg := range os.Args[1:] {
#             if arg == "-v" || arg == "--version" { ... } }
#       → applyWorkDir() reads constants.WorkDirEnv via
#         os.Getenv
#   This entry is the Go=150 leader bump (R970 round-number
#   commit landmark) that continues Axis 95 (Stripe / async-
#   stripe) opened at R969 with Rust=async-stripe via
#   devflowinc/trieve (the round-number Rust=150 landmark).
#
#   No completion for `passwall-server` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_passwall-server() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(-v --version)'{-v,--version}'[print version info and exit]'
}

_passwall-server "$@"
